# Why Use Unplugged Activites to Teach Computational Thinking? 

#### Unplugged activities provide a **hands-on, accessible** way for students to engage with computational thinking concepts before they start coding.

#### By removing the complexity of syntax and technology, these activities help students focus on fundamental problem-solving skills in a way that is interactive and inclusive.

## Benefits of Unplugged Activites: 

<br>

<div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; max-width: 900px; margin: auto;">

  
<div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 15px;">
